HEADWORD: Interlunary
<hw>In`ter*lu"na*ry</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>inter-</ets> +
<ets>lunar</ets>: cf. L. <ets>interlunis</ets>.]</ety> <def>Belonging or
pertaining to the time when the moon, at or near its conjunction with
the sun, is invisible.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

